{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 19:45:07.798268", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and context\n- Topology: Multi-tier Clos (fat-tree) using EBGP with FRR. One super-spine (AS 65000), two spines, and two leaves in the provided excerpt. Each leaf connects to a host: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 via 10.0.0.1) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 via 10.0.1.1).\n- Goal: Detect anomalies, localize faulty devices, and identify root cause based on current state.\n\nHigh-level health assessment\n- Data-plane: Host reachability tested across a subset of endpoints shows 0% packet loss and low RTTs, indicating traffic is forwarding. However, the subset provided did not explicitly include pc_0_0 ↔ pc_0_1, but overall fabric reachability appears healthy.\n- Control-plane: One spine (spine_router_0_1) has BGP completely down with all its neighbors. The rest of the fabric (including spine_router_0_0 and super_spine_router_0) has BGP adjacencies up and is exchanging routes as expected.\n\nDetailed findings and evidence\n\n1) Hosts\n- pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 — interface up, routes correct.\n- pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1 — interface up, routes correct.\n\n2) Leaf routers\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200)\n  - BGP summary: 3 neighbors Established, 1 neighbor Active:\n    - Neighbor 172.16.0.40 (remote AS 65101) is Active (not established).\n    - Other neighbors (e.g., 172.16.0.32, .48, .56) are Established with PfxRcd=7.\n  - Routing table: All non-local 10.x/24 routes learned via 172.16.0.32 (spine_router_0_0). The /31 links show 172.16.0.40/31 connected on eth1 (the link toward spine_router_0_1), but no BGP routes via that link.\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201)\n  - BGP summary: 3 neighbors Established, 1 neighbor Active:\n    - Neighbor 172.16.0.42 (remote AS 65101) is Active.\n    - Other neighbors (e.g., 172.16.0.34, .50, .58) are Established with PfxRcd=7.\n  - Routing table: All non-local 10.x/24 routes learned via 172.16.0.34 (spine_router_0_0). The /31 link 172.16.0.42/31 connected on eth1 (toward spine_router_0_1) has no active BGP routes.\n\nInterpretation: Both leaves have their sessions to spine_router_0_1 down (Active state), and are forwarding all upstream traffic via spine_router_0_0. This indicates loss of uplink redundancy.\n\n3) Spine routers\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100)\n  - BGP summary: All 6 peers Established (super-spines and leaves). Receives and advertises expected /24 prefixes. ECMP present toward 10.1.x/24 via super-spine links 172.16.0.0 and 172.16.0.16.\n  - Routing table: Contains all expected 10.x/24 routes; /31 interconnects are correctly connected. This spine is healthy.\n\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65701)\n  - BGP summary: Peers 6, all in Idle with “Up/Down: never”, PfxRcd 0. RIB entries 0.\n  - Running config: router bgp 65701 (local AS 65701). Neighbors configured for remote-as 65000 (super-spine) and 65200–65203 (leaves).\n  - Routing table: Only connected /31 links; no BGP-learned routes.\n\nInterpretation: This spine has no established BGP sessions at all and is not participating in the control-plane.\n\n4) Super-spine (super_spine_router_0, AS 65000)\n- BGP summary:\n  - Neighbor 172.16.0.1 (spine_router_0_0, AS 65100): Established, PfxRcd 4 (as expected for a spine).\n  - Neighbor 172.16.0.3 (expected AS 65101): State Active, PfxRcd 0 — not established.\n  - Other neighbors Established.\n- Routing table: Healthy, with expected BGP routes.\n\nInterpretation: The super-spine is configured to peer with a spine at 172.16.0.3 expecting AS 65101, but cannot establish that session.\n\nAnomaly detection\n- Abnormal behavior: All BGP adjacencies to spine_router_0_1 are down (Idle/Active) from every neighbor’s perspective (leaves and super-spine). The fabric is operating in a degraded state with only spine_router_0_0 providing uplink connectivity for the leaves shown.\n\nFault localization\n- Faulty device: spine_router_0_1.\n- Supporting evidence:\n  - spine_router_0_1 BGP summary: all neighbors Idle, 0 routes.\n  - super_spine_router_0 sees neighbor 172.16.0.3 (the spine’s interface) in Active.\n  - Both leaves see their spine_router_0_1 neighbors (172.16.0.40 and 172.16.0.42) in Active.\n  - spine_router_0_0 is fully healthy, isolating the issue to the second spine.\n\nRoot cause analysis\n- Root cause: ASN mismatch on spine_router_0_1.\n  - Current configuration: router bgp 65701 (local AS 65701).\n  - Expected pattern: In this topology, each spine uses a specific AS (e.g., spine_router_0_0 uses AS 65100), and the super-spine is configured to peer with the other spine at AS 65101. The leaves also expect spine_router_0_1 to be AS 65101, as shown by their neighbor configs (remote-as 65101 on 172.16.0.40 and .42).\n  - Effect: EBGP session negotiation fails with all neighbors due to AS mismatch, keeping sessions in Idle/Active and preventing any route exchange via spine_router_0_1.\n\nImpact\n- Current traffic still forwards successfully via spine_router_0_0; hosts exhibit good reachability and low latency.\n- However, the fabric has lost path diversity and redundancy via spine_router_0_1. Any failure on spine_router_0_0 or its links would severely impact connectivity for the affected leaves. Load-sharing and resilience are degraded.\n\nConclusion\n- The network is functionally forwarding traffic but in a degraded state due to a control-plane failure localized to spine_router_0_1. The root cause is a misconfigured local AS (65701) on spine_router_0_1 that does not match the neighbors’ expected AS (65101), preventing EBGP adjacencies from forming.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11663, "output_tokens": 4716, "total_tokens": 16379, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3136}}}
